ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a course that will give you a well rounded knowledge base in the MOS field after taking it.I will recommend this course to my fellow students.Because it involves more than just listening and doing homework. We also have to do research on one topic and try to consolidate our findings into a long presentation, which was not easy but extremely beneficial in terms of acquiring the knowledge.
It is a good seminar style course. I would recommend this class for someone who would like perspective and depth, but would say they should have previous exposure to some of the material.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I am a PhD student in MOS field. I would say this course helps me grasp a broad-range of view in this MOS field, and Prof Ma's profound knowledge in this field helped me to get to know the history of the whole development of this one of the biggest industry and how technology advancement propels the industry. To this end, this course motivated me a lot to pursue a research career in MOS area.
This helped me develop motivation and understanding of applications for some of the research that I do.
